com.storytron.uber

Class Verb

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.storytron.uber.Word
      • com.storytron.uber.Verb
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Word>

    public final class Verb
extends Word
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable
    This class represents a verb. A verb expresses all the variations in which a certain action can occur. It is the root of a hierarchy of conditions and behaviors that comprehends Roles, Role.Options and Role.Option.OptionWordSockets. Scripts are intensively used to tell those conditions and behaviors.

    The verb manages a collections of Roles and a collection of consequence Scripts.

    Roles are manipulated through the methods #addRole(Deikto, Role), #addRole(Deikto, int, Role), #addRole(Deikto, String, boolean), #deleteRole(Deikto, int), getRoleCount(), #getRoleIndex(Role), getRole(int), getRoleIndex(String), getRoles().

    Consequences are scripts executed when an event of the verb happens. They can be manipulated through the methods addConsequence(Operator), #addConsequence(Script), addConsequence(int, Script), getConsequence(int), getConsequence(String), getConsequenceCount(), getConsequenceIndex(String), getConsequences().

    The following attributes can be set through getters and setters: hijackable, occupiesDirObject, timeToPrepare, timeToExecute, audience, category, expression, trivial_Momentous, description, abortScript.

    For each wordsocket, the Verb tells if the wordsocket is used with the method isWordSocketActive(int) and controls activation of the wordsocket with the method #setWordSocketIsActive(int, boolean).
